sections.heading: Evidence; instrument; written and printed matter; writing controls
sections.text: When an instrument consists partly of written and partly of printed form, the former controls the latter, where the two are inconsistent.SourceR.S.1867, Code ยง 340, p. 451;R.S.1913, ยง 7908;C.S.1922, ยง 8850;C.S.1929, ยง 20-1216;R.S.194
